tedAt":"2023-10-11T23:27:46Z","mergedAt":null,"labels":{"nodes":[{"name":"dependencies"}]},"comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"samcoe","name":"Sam Coe","company":"@github "},"body":"Closing in favor of https://github.com/cli/gh-webhook/pull/27","createdAt":"2023-10-12T12:10:40Z"},{"author":{"login":"dependabot"},"body":"OK, I won't notify you again about this release, but will get in touch when a new version is available. If you'd rather skip all updates until the next major or minor version, let me know by commenting `@dependabot ignore this major version` or `@dependabot ignore this minor version`.\n\nIf you change your mind, just re-open this PR and I'll resolve any conflicts on it.","createdAt":"2023-10-12T12:10:43Z"}]},"reviews":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":27,"title":"Update dependencies and Go to version 1.21","author":{"login":"samcoe","name":"Sam Coe","email":"","company":"@github ","bio":"","location":null,"createdAt":"2014-06-23T23:09:52Z"},"createdAt":"2023-10-12T12:10:03Z","mergedAt":"2023-10-12T15:15:39Z","labels":{"nodes":[]},"comments":{"nodes":[]},"reviews":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"kklopfenstein","name":"Kevin Klopfenstein","company":null},"state":"APPROVED","createdAt":"2023-10-12T13:58:05Z"}]}},{"number":31,"title":"Bump golang.org/x/net from 0.17.0 to 0.23.0","author":{"login":"dependabot"},"createdAt":"2024-04-19T12:16:21Z","mergedAt":null,"labels":{"nodes":[{"name":"dependencies"}]},"comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","company":"GitHub"},"body":"@dependabot rebase","createdAt":"2025-01-02T19:56:34Z"},{"author":{"login":"dependabot"},"body":"Looks like golang.org/x/net is no longer a dependency, so this is no longer needed.","createdAt":"2025-01-02T19:57:16Z"}]},"reviews":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":34,"title":"Bump github.com/cli/go-gh/v2 from 2.4.0 to 2.11.1","author":{"login":"dependabot"},"createdAt":"2024-12-17T13:01:30Z","mergedAt":"2025-01-02T19:17:40Z","labels":{"nodes":[{"name":"dependencies"}]},"comments":{"nodes":[]},"reviews":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":37,"title":"Bump github.com/cli/go-gh/v2 from 2.11.1 to 2.12.1","author":{"login":"dependabot"},"createdAt":"2025-05-30T15:39:30Z","mergedAt":"2025-10-21T15:33:11Z","labels":{"nodes":[{"name":"dependencies"},{"name":"go"}]},"comments":{"nodes":[]},"reviews":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","company":"GitHub"},"state":"APPROVED","createdAt":"2025-10-21T15:32:57Z"}]}},{"number":39,"title":"Add MIT license file","author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","email":"","company":"GitHub","bio":"Crunchy PB 🤝 Smooth PB","location":"Alberta, Canada","createdAt":"2019-02-06T16:33:47Z"},"createdAt":"2025-10-21T15:36:02Z","mergedAt":"2025-10-21T16:03:04Z","labels":{"nodes":[]},"comments":{"nodes":[]},"reviews":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"mxie","name":"Melissa Xie","company":"@github"},"state":"COMMENTED","createdAt":"2025-10-21T15:38:14Z"},{"author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","company":"GitHub"},"state":"COMMENTED","createdAt":"2025-10-21T16:00:05Z"},{"author":{"login":"mxie","name":"Melissa Xie","company":"@github"},"state":"APPROVED","createdAt":"2025-10-21T16:01:37Z"}]}},{"number":40,"title":"Update GitHub Actions to use newer versions","author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","email":"","company":"GitHub","bio":"Crunchy PB 🤝 Smooth PB","location":"Alberta, Canada","createdAt":"2019-02-06T16:33:47Z"},"createdAt":"2025-10-21T16:20:42Z","mergedAt":"2025-10-21T16:21:17Z","labels":{"nodes":[]},"comments":{"nodes":[]},"reviews":{"nodes":[]}}],"pageInfo":{"hasNextPage":false,"endCursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpHOruGYZA=="}},"issues":{"nodes":[{"number":1,"title":"## What's Changed","author":{"login":"Nm980mn","name":null,"email":"","company":null,"bio":null,"location":null},"createdAt":"2022-10-18T09:51:01Z","closedAt":"2022-10-24T10:59:41Z","comments":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":6,"title":"Simulate `installation` key in event body","author":{"login":"gr2m","name":"Gregor Martynus","email":"","company":"@vercel @octokit @octoherd @probot @nock @semantic-release @AllContributors @hearts","bio":"AI SDK tech lead","location":"Los Angeles"},"createdAt":"2022-11-04T06:59:43Z","closedAt":null,"comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"gr2m","name":"Gregor Martynus","company":"@vercel @octokit @octoherd @probot @nock @semantic-release @AllContributors @hearts"},"body":"I think a much simpler approach might be to just pass the installation id as CLI argument\r\n\r\n```\r\n--installation 123\r\n```\r\n\r\nand the plugin would add the `installation` key to the event payload based on it\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  \"installation\": {\r\n    \"id\": 123\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nGitHub also sets `installation.node_id`, but at least from my experience, that key is not needed. `installation.id` is all that's required in order to create the installation access key"},{"author":{"login":"gr2m","name":"Gregor Martynus","company":"@vercel @octokit @octoherd @probot @nock @semantic-release @AllContributors @hearts"},"body":"Yet another approach might be to set some kind of special header so that the app code knows it's run in a dev environment and need to get the installation by itself. The app already has access to the repository and the GitHub App credentials, that's all that is needed. It could be built into the GitHub App SDKs such as https://github.com/octokit/app.js. But I think I would prefer the other two options mentioned above, so we don't need different behavior depending on environment"}]}},{"number":11,"title":"\"Error: you must be authenticated to run this command\", despite being authenticated","author":{"login":"QuantumToasted","name":"Daniel Jarski","email":"","company":null,"bio":"","location":null},"createdAt":"2023-04-12T01:42:59Z","closedAt":"2023-05-26T11:43:17Z","comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"QuantumToasted","name":"Daniel Jarski","company":null},"body":"Upon further inspection, it seems https://github.com/cli/gh-webhook/blob/b8fb5686ed688da846f68eb2cc96f517d451712f/webhook/forward.go#L72-L75 isn't functioning as intended on my installation.\r\n\r\nFollowing the rabbit hole led me to the `auth` module in the `go-gh` repo, specifically https://github.com/cli/go-gh/blob/026e976b60f91b35bd97a2d82914c24515dda127/pkg/auth/auth.go#L35-L52.\r\n\r\nIt tries to first read from $GITHUB_TOKEN or an appropriate config file(?), then it tries to effectively return the value of `gh auth token` by finding the path to `gh.exe`, by first using `$GH_PATH` then falling back to `safeexec.LookPath(\"gh\")`. I don't know what safeexec does to find the location of the executable, but neither setting `$GH_PATH` nor letting it \"find\" the executable seems to function correctly in my circumstance. This is likely not an issue with `gh-webhook` specifically.\r\n\r\nI was able to resolve this issue by setting the envvar `$GITHUB_TOKEN` and token lookup now works fine. If appropriate, feel free to transfer this issue to the correct repo"},{"author":{"login":"stoe","name":"Stefan Stölzle","company":"@github"},"body":"I think https://github.com/cli/gh-webhook/pull/9 will fix this. \n\nJust waiting on review. "}]}},{"number":18,"title":"Hook.name is invalid","author":{"login":"cliveza","name":"Clive Zagno","email":"","company":null,"bio":"This is me, my stuff is here http://github.com/zagno","location":null},"createdAt":"2023-07-11T17:41:58Z","closedAt":"2023-07-18T17:27:33Z","comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"samcoe","name":"Sam Coe","company":"@github "},"body":"cc @cli/webhooks to investigate"},{"author":{"login":"yxnyxnyxnyxnyxnyxn","name":"Sydney ","company":null},"body":"👋 @cliveza We are not support webhook forwarding in GHES\r\nWe recently updated our doc https://github.com/github/webhook-forwarder/pull/65. "},{"author":{"login":"CleanCut","name":"Nathan Stocks","company":"@agileperception "},"body":"To clarify, webhook forwarding is supported only on github.com. Other GitHub products such as GitHub Enterprise (GHES) are not supported.\r\n\r\nTo accomplish the same task in GHES, you could use a third-party proxying solution. I don't have any specific recommendations, but I am aware that others have used https://ngrok.com/ and https://smee.io/"}]}},{"number":19,"title":"Document `webhook-forwarder.github.com` api","author":{"login":"dhirschfeld","name":"Dave Hirschfeld","email":"dave.hirschfeld@gmail.com","company":null,"bio":"Full-Stack Analytics Engineer","location":"Brisbane, Australia"},"createdAt":"2023-09-06T00:58:22Z","closedAt":null,"comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"gr2m","name":"Gregor Martynus","company":"@vercel @octokit @octoherd @probot @nock @semantic-release @AllContributors @hearts"},"body":"I implemented a relay in JavaScript that you could use as a reference for the time being:\r\nhttps://github.com/gr2m/github-webhook-relay/"},{"author":{"login":"dhirschfeld","name":"Dave Hirschfeld","company":null},"body":"Awesome, thanks for sharing @gr2m! "}]}},{"number":28,"title":"Did the websocket message payload keys change to lowercase?","author":{"login":"gr2m","name":"Gregor Martynus","email":"","company":"@vercel @octokit @octoherd @probot @nock @semantic-release @AllContributors @hearts","bio":"AI SDK tech lead","location":"Los Angeles"},"createdAt":"2023-10-23T17:56:17Z","closedAt":null,"comments":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":32,"title":"Forwarding localhost gives `http: server gave HTTP response to HTTPS client`","author":{"login":"ketozhang","name":"Keto D. Zhang","email":"keto.zhang@gmail.com","company":"@Caltech-IPAC ","bio":"Research Software Engineer working on the NASA Roman Space Telescope @Caltech-IPAC ","location":null},"createdAt":"2024-07-16T21:27:59Z","closedAt":null,"comments":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":35,"title":"gh pr checkout 102","author":null,"createdAt":"2024-12-25T17:50:51Z","closedAt":"2024-12-25T17:51:30Z","comments":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":38,"title":"license information","author":{"login":"koibtw","name":"june","email":"me@koi.rip","company":null,"bio":"👻 @comfysage • pfp by @roku6226 on twitter","location":null},"createdAt":"2025-10-21T00:39:59Z","closedAt":"2025-10-21T16:03:05Z","comments":{"nodes":[{"author":{"login":"BagToad","name":"Kynan Ware","company":"GitHub"},"body":"@adamperkowski Thanks for bringing this up! I added a license in #39 👍 🍻 "}]}}],"pageInfo":{"hasNextPage":false,"endCursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNS0xMC0yMVQwMDozOTo1OVrO0qrudQ=="}}}}}]